quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  27,83,On that Day We shall assemble together a host from every community of those who cried lies to Our revelations and they will be grouped
  27,84,"then, when they have arrived, He will say, \"Did you deny My revelations, even though you did not have proper knowledge of them? Or what was it that you were doing"
  27,85,"The verdict will be given against them, because they did wrong, and they will be speechless"
  27,86,Do they not see that We have made the night for them to rest in and the day to give them light? There are certainly signs in that for people who believe
  27,87,"On the Day when the trumpet is blown, whoever is in the heavens and whoever is on the earth will be struck with terror, except for those whom God wishes to spare. All shall come to Him in utter humility"
  27,88,"You see the mountains and think them firmly fixed. But they shall pass away as the clouds pass away. Such is the work of God, who has ordered all things to perfection: He is fully aware of what you do"
  27,89,"Whoever does a good deed, shall be rewarded with what is better, and will be secure from fear of that Day"
  27,90,and those who do evil will be flung down on their faces in the Fire. Are you not rewarded according to your deeds
  27,91,"Say, \"I am commanded to serve the Lord of this town, which He has made inviolable and to whom everything belongs; I am commanded to be one of those devoted to Him"
  27,92,"to recite the Quran.\" Whoever follows its guidance, follows it only for the good of his own soul; and as for him who goes astray, just say, \"I am only a warner"
  27,93,"Then say, \"Praise be to God! He will show you His signs and you will recognize them. Your Lord is not unaware of what you do"